<package name="KEYSTONE-1035">
<description>&lt;h1&gt;Keystone 1035&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The part is .039 inch (1.00mm) wide. The drill needs to be a bit bigger since the through-hole plating will make it smaller again. Since 1 oz copper is .0014 inch thick, then the hole should be drilled at least .003 larger, or .042.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Note that a hole size of .045 was tried at JLCPCB and it was too sloppy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<pad name="P$1" x="0" y="0" drill="1.0668"/>
<text x="-1.27" y="1.27" size="0.8128" layer="25" font="vector" ratio="16">&gt;NAME</text>
<text x="-1.27" y="-2.54" size="0.8128" layer="27" font="vector" ratio="16">&gt;VALUE</text>
</package>
<package name="KEYSTONE-4952">
<description>&lt;h1&gt;Keystone 4952&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The part is .047 inch wide. The drill needs to be a bit bigger since the through-hole plating will make it smaller again. Since 1 oz copper is .0014 inch thick, then the hole should be drilled at least .003 larger, or .050.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<pad name="P$1" x="0" y="0" drill="1.27"/>
</package>
